The paper deals with 3D object representation and retrieval, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and computer graphics (cs.GR). The proposed approach involves learning a joint embedding space using a 3D CNN-based approach, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper also introduces a new dataset for evaluation, which involves annotation and ranking of scan-CAD similarity, indicating a potential focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
